&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Instructor - IUCT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a band 4 Technical Instructor to join our Integrated Urgent Care Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We provide Urgent Care and rehabilitation to adults within the community aiming to promote independence, prevent hospital admission and support discharges from hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be an active member of the Urgent Care Team. You will work within the Multi-Disciplinary Team to assist and support registered nurses and therapists in a range of patient care activities, assisting patients with activities of daily living, to promote faster recovery from illness and maximize independent living.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post is based in the community, a full driving license and car is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will work 5 days over a 7 Day period and work shifts of 8am-4pm or 2pm-10pm and work alternate weekends on a rota basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews TBC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Joanne Walker&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Business Support Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Joanne.walker@tgh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0161 342 5238&lt;/p&gt;
